The paper discusses an algorithm for computing isogenies between elliptic curves, which is relevant to cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithm also involves computational complexity and memory requirements, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of elliptic curves and finite fields suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions a variant of the algorithm that requires only polynomial memory, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
